1
00:00:02,480 --> 00:00:04,560
I'll see you again, mister.

2
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,120
(ALARM BLARING)

3
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:40,560
Stop that. Stop it!

4
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:45,200
What was all that about, eh? Eh?

5
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:48,800
-What's your problem?
-Right. Just settle down now.

6
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,520
-Excuse me.
-So sorry.

7
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,320
-What!
-What?

8
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,760
What?

9
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,360
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

10
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:40,240
-Who are you?
-Oh, brilliant.

11
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,320
I mean, totally wrong, big emergency,

12
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,280
universe goes bang
in five minutes, but...

13
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:46,720
-Brilliant!
-I'm the Doctor. Who are you?

14
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:50,440
-Yes, you are. You are the Doctor.
-Yes, I am. I'm the Doctor.

15
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:54,080
Oh, good for you, Doctor.
Good for brilliant old you.

16
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:56,240
Is there something wrong with you?

17
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:59,680
Oh, there it goes, the frowny face.
I remember that one.

18
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:03,160
Mind you, bit saggier than
it ought to be. Hair's a bit greyer.

19
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,680
That's 'cause of me, though.

20
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,480
Two of us together's shorted out
the time differential.

21
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,520
It should all snap back in place
when we get you home.

22
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:12,200
Be able to close that coat again.
But never mind that. Look at you!

23
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:17,120
The hat, the coat, the crickety
cricket stuff, the stick of celery...

24
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,240
Brave choice, celery.
But fair play to you,

25
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:21,160
not a lot of men can carry off
a decorative vegetable.

26
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,840
Shut up!

27
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,480
There is something wrong with my Tardis

28
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,920
and I've got to do something about it
very, very quickly.

29
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,040
And it would help, it really would help,

30
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,200
if there wasn't some skinny idiot
ranting in my face

31
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,960
about every single thing
that happens to be in front of him.

32
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:40,720
-Ooh, okay. Sorry, Doctor.
-Thank you.

33
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,720
-0Oh, the back of our head!
-What?

34
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,760
Sorry, sorry. It's not something
you see every day, is it?

35
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:49,440
The back of your own head.
Mind you, I can see why you wear a hat.

36
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:52,400
I don't want to seem vain,
but could you keep that on?

37
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,960
What have you done to my Tardis?

38
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,760
You've changed the desktop theme,
haven't you?

39
00:02:56,840 --> 00:03:00,840
What's this one? Coral?
It's worse than the leopard skin.

40
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:04,200
Oh! And out they come, the brainy specs.

41
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:06,800
You don't even need them. You just think
they make you look a bit clever.

42
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,200
(ALARM BLARING)

43
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:12,840
That's an alert. Level Five,
indicating a temporal collision.

44
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:16,320
It's like two Tardises
have merged, but...

45
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,400
There's definitely only
one Tardis present.

46
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:23,880
It's like two time zones at war
in the heart of the Tardis.

47
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,560
That's a paradox.

48
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:30,200
It could blow a hole in
the space-time continuum the size of ...

49
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,480
(WHIRRING)

50
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,400
Well, actually,
the exact size of Belgium.

51
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,320
That's a bit undramatic,
isn't it? Belgium?

52
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,120
-Need this?
-No, I'm fine.

53
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,840
Oh, no, of course.
You mostly went hands-free, didn't you?

54
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:45,640
Like, "I'm the Doctor. I can save the
universe using a kettle and some string.

55
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:48,480
“And look at me,
I'm wearing a vegetable "

56
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:52,120
-Who are you?
-Take a look.

57
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:56,280
-Oh. Oh, no.
-Oh, yes.

58
00:03:56,360 --> 00:04:00,040
-You're... Oh, no, you're...
-Here it comes, yeah. Yeah, I am.

59
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,800
-A fan.
-Yeah... What?

60
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:06,440
Level 10 now. This is bad.
A few minutes to Belgium.

61
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:09,200
What do you mean, a fan?
I'm not just a fan, I'm you.

62
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:13,280
Okay, you're my biggest fan.
Look, it's perfectly understandable.

63
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,320
I go zooming around space and time,
saving planets,

64
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,040
fighting monsters and being...

65
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,160
Well, let's be honest,
pretty sort of marvellous.

66
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:23,240
So naturally, now and then, people
notice me. Start up their little groups.

67
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:26,720
That LI.N.D.A. lot.
Are you one of them?

68
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:31,440
How did you get in here?
Can't have you lot knowing where I live.

69
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,720
Listen to me. I'm you.
I'm you with a new face.

70
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,200
Check out this bone structure, Doctor,

71
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:37,120
'cause one day
you're going to be shaving it.

72
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,600
(BELL RINGING)

73
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,240
The cloister bell.

74
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,280
Yeah, right on time. That's my cue.

75
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,480
In less than a minute,
we're going to create a black hole

76
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:47,280
strong enough to
swallow the entire universe.

77
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,840
Yeah, that's my fault actually.
I was rebuilding the Tardis,

78
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,280
forgot to put the shields back up.

79
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,240
Your Tardis and my Tardis...
Well, the same Tardis

80
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,960
at different points in
its own time stream collided,

81
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:57,240
and there you go,
end of the universe, butterfingers.

82
00:04:57,320 --> 00:05:00,360
But don't worry, I know exactly
how this all works out. Watch.

83
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,800
Venting the thermo-buffer.

84
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,520
Roaring the Helmic Regulator!

85
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,360
And just to finish off,
let's fry those Ziton crystals.

86
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,320
-You'll blow up the Tardis.
-Only way out.

87
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,320
-Who told you that?
-You told me that.

88
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,120
(EXPLOSION)

89
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:24,600
Supernova and black hole
at the exact same instant.

90
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:28,640
-Explosion cancels out implosion.
-Matter remains constant.

91
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,920
-Brilliant.
-Far too brilliant.

92
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,560
I've never met anyone else
who could fly the Tardis like that.

93
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:34,720
Sorry, mate, you still haven't.

94
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:37,440
You didn't have time to work all
that out. Even I couldn't do it.

95
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:40,240
I didn't work it out. I didn't have to.

96
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,920
-You remembered.
-Because you will remember.

97
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:49,280
You remembered being me,
watching you doing that.

98
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:54,480
You only knew what to do
because I saw you do it.

99
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,680
Wibbly-wobbly...

100
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,640
BOTH: Timey-wimey!

101
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,840
(WHIRRING)

102
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:03,000
Right! Tardises are separating.
Sorry, Doctor. Time's up.

103
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,440
Back to long ago. Where are you now?

104
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,240
Nyssa and Tegan? Cybermen and Mara

105
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:09,320
and Time Lords in funny hats
and the Master?

106
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:11,360
Oh, he just showed up again.
Same as ever.

107
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:15,000
Oh, no. Really?
Does he still have that rubbish beard?

108
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,680
No. No, beard this time. Well, a wife.

109
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:24,200
Oh, I seem to be off. What can I say?

110
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,280
-Thank you, Doctor.
-Thank you.

111
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,000
I'm very welcome.

112
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:37,000
You know, I love being you.

113
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,040
Back when I first started
at the very beginning,

114
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,920
I was always trying to be old and grumpy
and important,

115
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,080
like you do when you're young.

116
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:48,200
And then I was you. And it was all
dashing about and playing cricket,

117
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,720
and my voice going all squeaky
when I shouted. I still do that!

118
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:53,000
The voice thing. I got that from you.

119
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,960
Oh, and the trainers and...

120
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:00,200
Snap.

121
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:02,440
"Cause you know what, Doctor?

122
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,120
You were my Doctor.

123
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:12,880
-To days to come.
-All my love to long ago.

124
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:25,200
FIFTH DOCTOR: Oh, Doctor.
Remember to put your shields up.

125
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,840
(HORN BLARING)

126
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,920
What?

127
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,040
What?

128
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:41,760
(BELL RINGING)

129
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,240
What?

